8.instruction:
Change the bet slip behavior to append new bets instead of replacing existing ones.

Current behavior (in BettingContext.tsx addToBetSlip function around line 72-86):
- When a new bet is clicked, it clears the entire bet slip and adds only the new bet: `setBetSlip([{ new bet }])`

Required behavior:
- When a new bet is clicked, append it to the existing bet slip: `setBetSlip([...betSlip, { new bet }])`
- If the same game already exists in the bet slip, replace that specific bet instead of adding a duplicate
- Keep the "Clear All" functionality to allow users to manually clear all bets

Implementation:
1. In `/workspace/shadcn-ui/src/contexts/BettingContext.tsx`, modify the addToBetSlip function (around lines 66-86)
2. Check if a bet for the same game already exists in betSlip
3. If it exists, replace that bet with the new one (update the bet type, odds, and values)
4. If it doesn't exist, append the new bet to the end of the betSlip array
5. Remove or update the debug console.log statements added earlier since they're no longer needed

Example logic:
```tsx
const addToBetSlip = (game: Game, betType: BetSlipItem['betType'], odds: number, value?: number) => {
  if (!user) {
    toast.error('Please login to place bets');
    return;
  }

  const newBet: BetSlipItem = {
    game,
    betType,
    odds,
    stake: 0,
    spreadValue: betType.includes('spread') ? value : undefined,
    totalValue: betType === 'over' || betType === 'under' ? value : undefined,
  };

  // Check if bet for this game already exists
  const existingBetIndex = betSlip.findIndex(item => item.game.id === game.id);

  if (existingBetIndex !== -1) {
    // Replace existing bet for this game
    const updatedBetSlip = [...betSlip];
    updatedBetSlip[existingBetIndex] = newBet;
    setBetSlip(updatedBetSlip);
  } else {
    // Append new bet to the end
    setBetSlip([...betSlip, newBet]);
  }
};
```

